{
    "blocks": [
        {
            "id": "intro_functions",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Function Basics",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "A function is a block of code that performs a specific task. Instead of writing the same code multiple times, you can put it in a function and **reuse** it whenever you need."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Functions help you organize your code and make it easier to understand and maintain."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "creating_functions",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Creating Functions",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "To create a function, use the `def` keyword, followed by the function name, parentheses `()`, and a colon `:`. The code inside the function must be indented."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def greet():\n    print(\"Hello!\")\n    print(\"Welcome!\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "This creates a function called `greet` that prints two messages."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "calling_functions",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "To use a function, you need to **call** it by writing its name followed by parentheses."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def greet():\n    print(\"Hello!\")\n    print(\"Welcome!\")\n\ngreet()",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Hello!\nWelcome!"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Calling `greet()` runs the code inside the function."
                }
            ]
        },
