        {
            "id": "reusing_functions",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The power of functions is **reusability**. You can call the same function multiple times."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def celebrate():\n    print(\"🎉 Congratulations!\")\n\ncelebrate()\ncelebrate()\ncelebrate()",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "🎉 Congratulations!\n🎉 Congratulations!\n🎉 Congratulations!"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "We called `celebrate()` three times without rewriting the code."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_reuse",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "What happens when you call a function twice?"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def show_message():\n    print(\"Hello\")\n\nshow_message()\nshow_message()",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "mcq",
                    "content": "",
                    "properties": {
                        "question": "",
                        "options": [
                            "Prints \"Hello\" once",
                            "Prints \"Hello\" twice",
                            "Error occurs"
                        ],
                        "correctAnswerIndex": 1,
                        "correctFeedback": "Correct! Each function call runs the code inside.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Each time you call a function, its code runs.",
                        "explanation": "Functions can be called multiple times, and each call executes the code inside."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "function_names",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Function names follow the same rules as variables: use lowercase with underscores for multiple words. Choose descriptive names that explain what the function does."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def calculate_total():\n    print(\"Calculating...\")\n\ndef send_email():\n    print(\"Sending email...\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Good function names make your code easier to understand."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_naming",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Which is a good function name?"
                },
                {
